cb865f2595fd3d5f23"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1332602 - ArrayBufferObject::create should throw RangeError if the input is bigger than INT32_MAX. r=evilpie, a=jcristau", "files": ["dom/base/FileReader.cpp", "js/src/vm/ArrayBufferObject.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "11a92eecc2bbd51957cc677087f1a5d4d5cdbba8", "parents": ["0862625a6d9d0d5ccf7e83a9c66403941eea3c6b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1332602 - Propagate JS errors in FileReader. r=smaug, a=jcristau", "files": ["dom/base/FileReader.cpp", "dom/base/FileReader.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e52e3bd70e084fd880c8c52fadfa91b06e7f1566", "parents": ["11a92eecc2bbd51957cc677087f1a5d4d5cdbba8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hannes Verschore \u003chv1989@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334129 - TraceLogger - On destruction remove the logger from the mainlogger list. r=bbouvier, a=jcristau", "files": ["js/src/vm/Runtime.cpp", "js/src/vm/Runtime.h", "js/src/vm/TraceLogging.cpp", "js/src/vm/TraceLogging.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4b91754cb34934159a20c8c7f208b107169f727a", "parents": ["e52e3bd70e084fd880c8c52fadfa91b06e7f1566"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334647 - Make canvas.drawImage trigger a JS error rather than a critical error on an invalid target. r=rhunt, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3TxJM0tjhVC", "files": ["dom/canvas/CanvasRenderingContext2D.cpp", "dom/canvas/crashtests/1334647-1.html", "dom/canvas/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a9ef277d777fea3ef7e90d9b161df9bb678c8cd5", "parents": ["4b91754cb34934159a20c8c7f208b107169f727a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bob Clary \u003cbclary@bclary.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1328301 - Handle push/pull directory semantics changes in adb 1.0.36 for adb.py. r=gbrown, a=test-only", "files": ["testing/mozbase/mozdevice/mozdevice/adb.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0b9bce076847f575054fcdada642244724a50cde", "parents": ["a9ef277d777fea3ef7e90d9b161df9bb678c8cd5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bob Clary \u003cbclary@bclary.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1328301 - Handle push/pull directory semantics changes in adb 1.0.36 for devicemanagerADB. r=gbrown, a=test-only", "files": ["testing/mozbase/mozdevice/mozdevice/devicemanagerADB.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cd87cd1ee14ed5741be3ead8e491ee77e64e67d0", "parents": ["0b9bce076847f575054fcdada642244724a50cde"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bob Clary \u003cbclary@bclary.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334613 - [mozdevice] - Use root to kill processes on Android 7+. r=gbrown, a=test-only", "files": ["testing/mozbase/mozdevice/mozdevice/devicemanagerADB.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f271c045f7abe68f3c4e650f3901be6f32892b48", "parents": ["cd87cd1ee14ed5741be3ead8e491ee77e64e67d0"], "tags": []}], "date": 1485891765, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6853": {"changesets": [{"author": "David Keeler \u003cdkeeler@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1328718 - Implement system add-on to facilitate rollout of disabling SHA-1. r=Felipe, r=jcj, data-review=bsmedberg, a=jcristau", "files": ["browser/extensions/disableSHA1rollout/README.md", "browser/extensions/disableSHA1rollout/bootstrap.js", "browser/extensions/disableSHA1rollout/install.rdf.in", "browser/extensions/disableSHA1rollout/moz.build", "browser/extensions/moz.build", "testing/talos/talos/xtalos/xperf_whitelist.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6b6f15c4beceef5b055756bc18317262779f816f", "parents": ["f271c045f7abe68f3c4e650f3901be6f32892b48"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nihanth Subramanya \u003cnhnt11@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1313568 - Handle captive portal UI in per-window script. r=MattN, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FxjE2NblJe4\n* * *\nBug 1313568 - Update CaptivePortalWatcher tests to work with per-window handling of captive portal UI. r=MattN\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LXjaP37l2dQ\n* * *\nBug 1313568 - Remove CaptivePortalWatcher.jsm and move tests to browser/base/content/tests/captivePortal. r=MattN\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3dSsLNmSUMA", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser-captivePortal.js", "browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/base/content/global-scripts.inc", "browser/base/content/test/captivePortal/browser.ini", "browser/base/content/test/captivePortal/browser_CaptivePortalWatcher.js", "browser/base/content/test/captivePortal/browser_captivePortal_certErrorUI.js", "browser/base/jar.mn", "browser/components/nsBrowserGlue.js", "browser/modules/CaptivePortalWatcher.jsm", "browser/modules/moz.build", "browser/modules/test/browser.ini", "browser/modules/test/browser_CaptivePortalWatcher.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "603587ec2ecdd948558249e7543e8424c7fa4e57", "parents": ["6b6f15c4beceef5b055756bc18317262779f816f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nihanth Subramanya \u003cnhnt11@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1333075 - Ensure captive portal notification is displayed in all windows after portal is detected when none have focus. r=MattN, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9dvZp9Kn6kT", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser-captivePortal.js", "browser/base/content/test/captivePortal/browser_CaptivePortalWatcher.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c2d975acbc8308d51d39e006f2fb873869fbd488", "parents": ["603587ec2ecdd948558249e7543e8424c7fa4e57"], "tags": []}], "date": 1485895877, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6854": {"changesets": [{"author": "Matthew Noorenberghe \u003cmozilla@noorenberghe.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1333256 - Bring back the insecure field warning Learn More text in bold on beta. r=adw l10n=flod  a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8Z6pKwFqk3M", "files": ["toolkit/components/passwordmgr/LoginManagerContent.jsm", "toolkit/components/passwordmgr/test/mochitest/test_insecure_form_field_autocomplete.html", "toolkit/components/passwordmgr/test/unit/test_user_autocomplete_result.js", "toolkit/content/widgets/autocomplete.xml", "toolkit/locales/en-US/chrome/passwordmgr/passwordmgr.properties"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c16a0fc964a5790de244fc3ea3bb5c3d3c18d071", "parents": ["c2d975acbc8308d51d39e006f2fb873869fbd488"], "tags": []}], "date": 1485904437, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "mozilla@noorenberghe.ca"}, "6855": {"changesets": [{"author": "Matthew Noorenberghe \u003cmozilla@noorenberghe.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1333256 - Follow-up to fix test_password_field_autocomplete.html. a=bustage\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LBpCQNVyVFE", "files": ["toolkit/components/passwordmgr/test/mochitest/test_password_field_autocomplete.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f39a49e249ecea5f35bc096657fc778619ba60fd", "parents": ["c16a0fc964a5790de244fc3ea3bb5c3d3c18d071"], "tags": []}], "date": 1485909882, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "mozilla@noorenberghe.ca"}, "6856": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug, Automated blocklist update from host bld-linux64-spot-081 - a=blocklist-update", "files": ["browser/app/blocklist.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d6a060cc6210a9635b84e0cfad5c48d9adaa504e", "parents": ["f39a49e249ecea5f35bc096657fc778619ba60fd"], "tags": []}], "date": 1485949378, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "6857": {"changesets": [{"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1115055 - EditorEventListener::MouseDown() should check if mEditorBase is nullptr before calling its ForceCompositionEnd() r=smaug a=jcristau\n\nEditorEventListener::MouseDown() may be called by HTMLEditorEventListener::MouseDown() too.  In this case, mEditorBase may be nullptr.  Therefore, EditorEventListener::MouseDown() should check if mEditorBase is still available before using it.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1wAgPdt3db0", "files": ["editor/libeditor/EditorEventListener.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1f7f56f400f4a1e55349dc7742960e96e516c78c", "parents": ["d6a060cc6210a9635b84e0cfad5c48d9adaa504e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan Hunt \u003crhunt@eqrion.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1312881 - Add a telemetry probe to track the max scrollY of a page. r=jaws data-review=bsmedberg a=jcristau", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json", "toolkit/content/browser-content.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7ae89f085815b147c0c13ae75514235a00e1afb4", "parents": ["1f7f56f400f4a1e55349dc7742960e96e516c78c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1315450 EditorEventListener::MouseClick() should check if mEditorBase is available before calling its ForceCompositionEnd() r=smaug, a=jcristau\n\nIMEStateManager::OnClickInEditor() may cause anything because it may set input context.  For example, it may cause  opening VKB, changing focus or reflow.  So, mEditorBase here might have been gone.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: C0SVzb5SueS", "files": ["editor/libeditor/EditorEventListener.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "91fad2ff9219f13646839f547b85c8665bcd598f", "parents": ["7ae89f085815b147c0c13ae75514235a00e1afb4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Karl Tomlinson \u003ckarlt+@karlt.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1319353 - CreateCSSNode: Copy classes from the parent style context to its corresponding node in the path r=stransky+263117 a=jcristau\n\nThis is necessary for GTK to match CSS rules against classes on ancestor nodes\nof style contexts constructed from paths.\n\nIt can be tested with the following in ~/.config/gtk-3.0/gtk.css\n\ntooltip.background label {padding: 100px;}\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EUQ9ndeSl1Z", "files": ["widget/gtk/WidgetStyleCache.cpp", "widget/gtk/mozgtk/mozgtk.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ab3c86e35b57e4e5287effe39004c8172e7d7595", "parents": ["91fad2ff9219f13646839f547b85c8665bcd598f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1319660 - Fix possible crash when editing contentEditable; r=esawin r=masayuki r=smaug a=lizzard a=jcristau\n\nBug 1319660 - 1. Don't take shortcut if old replacement ranges don't match; r=esawin\n\nThe block at [1] is a shortcut we take when we reconcile Java text\nchanges with Gecko text changes. However, we only checked that the new\nranges are the same, i.e. that the new Gecko text is the same as the new\nJava text. We should also be checking that the old ranges are the same,\ni.e. that the replaced Gecko text is the same as the replaced Java text.\n\n[1] https://dxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/rev/bbbd2f7539f224a482cc6d2dd10e6a5f31c8baf3/mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/GeckoEditable.java#1233\n\nBug 1319660 - 2. Use previous node instead of sibling when adjusting last node; r=masayuki r=smaug\n\nnsContentIterator in pre mode adjusts its last node if the node is a\nchildless node like \u003cbr\u003e. However, right now it's using GetPrevSibling,\nwhich can lead to error in some edge cases such as:\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\nIn this case, if the last node is \u003cbr\u003e with offset 0, GetPrevSibling\nwill return \u003cp\u003e because \u003cp\u003e is \u003cbr\u003e's parent's previous sibling, and the\nlast node will be set to \u003cp\u003e. However, the correct last node in this\ncase is \u003cdiv\u003e, because \u003cbr\u003e with offset 0 refers to the position to the\nleft of \u003cbr\u003e, which is \u003cdiv\u003e with offset 0. In this case, PrevNode\nreturns the correct \u003cdiv\u003e value, so we should set the last node to the\nresult of PrevNode.\n\nFor the first node, for a childless node in pre mode, GetNextSibling and\nNextNode are the same, so there is no bug in this case. Nevertheless,\nthis patch changes the call to NextNode to be consistent with calling\nPrevNode for the last node.\n\nBug 1319660 - 3. Add test for correctly adjusting last node in content iterator; r=masayuki\n\nAdd a test for the previous patch that makes sure querying selected text\nin an edge case works correctly.\n\nBug 1319660 - 4. Add test for start node regression; r=me\n\nAdd a new test case for the NextNode() regression. r=me for trivial\ntest-only patch.\n\nBug 1319660 - 5. Restore GetNextSibling call for first node of pre-content-iterator; r=smaug\n\nThe last patch changed the `GetNextSibling()` call to `NextNode()`\nbecause I assumed they're equivalent in this case. That turned out to\nnot be the case because we can reach this line even if the node has\nchildren -- the index just has to be after the last child. So this patch\nrestores the `GetNextSibling` call to restore the correct behavior.\n\nI also added some comment to clarify that we can reach this line due to\none of two conditions: 1) the node has no children; 2) the node has\nchildren but the index is after the last child.\n\nThis patch also replaces the `HasChildren()` check when setting\n`cChild`.  If the index is after the last child (i.e. index ==\nchildCount), `GetChildAt()` fails and we erroneously log an assertion\nwarning, even though the input was valid. The new check handles all\ncases whether start node has children or not.", "files": ["dom/base/nsContentIterator.cpp", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/GeckoEditable.java", "widget/tests/window_composition_text_querycontent.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f3b2cabb6ced8147ff9eb5b16b9be45356c959d3", "parents": ["ab3c86e35b57e4e5287effe39004c8172e7d7595"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1327946 - Remove conditional moz-user-focus on identity block from urlbar. r=Gijs, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9F39TeDIGUf", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.css", "browser/base/content/browser.xul", "browser/base/content/test/siteIdentity/browser.ini", "browser/base/content/test/siteIdentity/browser_identityBlock_focus.js", "browser/base/content/test/siteIdentity/head.js", "browser/base/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "15c988d7b6a1724af64f720396cf9570cf74f7a8", "parents": ["f3b2cabb6ced8147ff9eb5b16b9be45356c959d3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florian Qu\u00e8ze \u003cflorian@queze.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1327953 - Fix enabling the 'Restore Default Search Engines' button when removing a default engine, r=Standard8 a=jcristau", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content/search.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aa531b36649210f09bf15803b98bc5b2c702cffd", "parents": ["15c988d7b6a1724af64f720396cf9570cf74f7a8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1328023 - Part 1. Don't use RangeUpdater except to composition transaction. r=masayuki, a=jcristau\n\nPart 3 fix of bug 1310912 is incorrect for not composition transaction.  PlaceholderTransation is for saving and restoring current selection for undo. So we shouldn't use range updater to normal transaction.\n\nComposition transaction can modify multiple nodes and it merges text node for ime into single text node. So if current selection is into IME text node, it might be failed to restore selection by UndoTransaction. So we need update selection by range updater to work UndoTransaction.\n\nAlso, CompositionTransaction::UndoTransaction will set selection after committed text. So at finally, selection will set correct position that composition transaction wants.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1NcH32YoKPQ", "files": ["editor/libeditor/EditorBase.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6698c9784e3f42d6031d36c538aa5656f1ada99e", "parents": ["aa531b36649210f09bf15803b98bc5b2c702cffd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1328023 - Part 2. Add test for undo. r=masayuki, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6ZuluRWrYxb", "files": ["editor/libeditor/tests/mochitest.ini", "editor/libeditor/tests/test_bug1328023.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "47cff7384496e6c3cddee310676fa2baf1c8316b", "parents": ["6698c9784e3f42d6031d36c538aa5656f1ada99e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kearwood Gilbert \u003ckgilbert@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1328053 - Correct thumb position when shift-click scrolling r=mats a=jcristau\n\nDuring the refactoring of nsSliderFrame::SetCurrentPositionInternal in Bug 957445, one\nof the two calls to nsSliderFrame::UpdateAttribute was missed.  This resulted in the position,\nidentified with nsGkAtoms::curpos, not being updated immediately after the call to\nnsSliderFrame::SetCurrentThumbPosition\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6gedouG4OFX", "files": ["layout/xul/nsSliderFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "04c3a6ba0e1cad58fa35fc52a2ff1ee666f48472", "parents": ["47cff7384496e6c3cddee310676fa2baf1c8316b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Catalin Badea \u003ccatalin.badea392@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1333112 - Fix windowClient.Navigate leak. r=bkelly a=jcristau", "files": ["dom/promise/Promise.cpp", "dom/promise/PromiseWorkerProxy.h", "dom/workers/ServiceWorkerWindowClient.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f4892327fe526842766adeee3e1f570330abc6b4", "parents": ["04c3a6ba0e1cad58fa35fc52a2ff1ee666f48472"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Valentin Gosu \u003cvalentin.gosu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1333285 - Add null check to nsHttpPipeline::OnHeadersAvailable() r=mcmanus a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9vvpEIUtDkv", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpPipeline.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ed8e85c6f1cfd51627a2551192c9a5924277f8e2", "parents": ["f4892327fe526842766adeee3e1f570330abc6b4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1333734 - fix chrome password import if it contains items we can't read as a URI, r=mak a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CAwIVNz70hs", "files": ["browser/components/migration/ChromeProfileMigrator.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f13c827cdc49d5befa46036184561ef96b37b7ab", "parents": ["ed8e85c6f1cfd51627a2551192c9a5924277f8e2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bas Schouten \u003cbschouten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334102 - If the uploadRect is empty post-transform abort the function. The graphics driver may try to read from the given address even though it's told width or height are empty. r=milan a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DxNOzU0SNHK", "files": ["gfx/2d/HelpersD2D.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a788025765c668d4d6b18ccf8f62126d75d301ac", "parents": ["f13c827cdc49d5befa46036184561ef96b37b7ab"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao+bmo\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334444 - Fix \"[compact layout] Add \"Your Top Sites\" heading\" r=gijs, a=jcristau", "files": ["browser/base/content/newtab/grid.js", "browser/base/content/newtab/newTab.css", "browser/base/content/newtab/newTab.xhtml", "browser/themes/shared/newtab/newTab.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a42f620fc44a6483953c1abb6e962e907f0e6157", "parents": ["a788025765c668d4d6b18ccf8f62126d75d301ac"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335306 Append active keyboard layout information into crash report when NativeKey crashes due to detecting impossible case caused by 3rd party's keyboard layout or utils r=m_kato a=jcristau\n\nWhen NativeKey crashes by itself, it means that we detect an impossible situation in usual environment. In such case, active 3rd party's keyboard layout or something other utility may hook API and returns odd result to us.\n\nFor investigating the cause and deciding what we should do in such cases, we should collect active keyboard layout name via crash reports.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HYRj24GwDHZ", "files": ["widget/windows/KeyboardLayout.cpp", "widget/windows/KeyboardLayout.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e80cbae08ecb0b43585f609758c8540de66d31a8", "parents": ["a42f620fc44a6483953c1abb6e962e907f0e6157"], "tags": []}], "date": 1485962960, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6858": {"changesets": [{"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1333233 - part 1: add telemetry for error counts from undo operations, r=bsmedberg,Dolske, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EdelbiibVWi", "files": ["browser/components/migration/AutoMigrate.jsm", "browser/components/migration/tests/unit/test_automigration.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7496413fecb8d6c5349db408c8689294e163877d", "parents": ["e80cbae08ecb0b43585f609758c8540de66d31a8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1333233 - part 2: add telemetry for the time it takes to do individual undo operations, r=bsmedberg,Dolske a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Lf7roH3EswB", "files": ["browser/components/migration/AutoMigrate.jsm", "browser/components/migration/tests/unit/test_automigration.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "44777332a82750e2440b88f61a8db6b463377665", "parents": ["7496413fecb8d6c5349db408c8689294e163877d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1485963613, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6859": {"changesets": [{"author": "Steve Fink \u003csfink@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1322559 - Grab the registers when using LUL. r=jseward, a=jcristau", "files": ["tools/profiler/core/GeckoSampler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d13a909fc8a10c8a691f4fc386b290a995d18f32", "parents": ["44777332a82750e2440b88f61a8db6b463377665"], "tags": []}], "date": 1485964156, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6860": {"changesets": [{"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 15c988d7b6a1 (bug 1327946) for failing own test browser_identityBlock_focus.js. r=backout a=backout on a CLOSED TREE", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.css", "browser/base/content/browser.xul", "browser/base/content/test/siteIdentity/browser.ini", "browser/base/content/test/siteIdentity/browser_identityBlock_focus.js", "browser/base/content/test/siteIdentity/head.js", "browser/base/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "964388f3501946027b15ef9af6e6bca2f4096552", "parents": ["d13a909fc8a10c8a691f4fc386b290a995d18f32"], "tags": []}], "date": 1485971395, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "6861": {"changesets": [{"author": "J. Ryan Stinnett \u003cjryans@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1313933 - Cleanup logging in RDM tab remoteness test. r=ochameau a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LSZGbhd6wg7\n", "files": ["devtools/client/responsive.html/test/browser/browser_tab_remoteness_change.js", "devtools/client/responsive.html/test/browser/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7ae2c069b120e60447044dfff9b682652825e14a", "parents": ["964388f3501946027b15ef9af6e6bca2f4096552"], "tags": []}, {"author": "J. Ryan Stinnett \u003cjryans@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1313933 - Explicitly bypass history when loading RDM UI. r=ochameau a=jcristau\n\nBy using `LOAD_FLAGS_BYPASS_HISTORY`, we can tell session history explicitly to\nignore the entry for the container UI (which is meant to remain hidden from the\nuser).\n\nThis allows us to remove the horrible racy hack that attempted to have the same\neffect.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LnhJpO9UbNI\n", "files": ["devtools/client/responsive.html/browser/swap.js", "devtools/client/responsive.html/browser/tunnel.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a15e503db4d1d7261680fb497af39b65babff013", "parents": ["7ae2c069b120e60447044dfff9b682652825e14a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1485978253, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "jryans@gmail.com"}, "6862": {"changesets": [{"author": "Matthew Noorenberghe \u003cmozilla@noorenberghe.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1332165 - Trim values for the purposes of 'skipEmptyFields' in _getPasswordFields. r=Dolske a=jcristau\n\nWe will no longer prompt to save passwords consisting solely of whitespace.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FknB39TCHEa", "files": ["toolkit/components/passwordmgr/LoginManagerContent.jsm", "toolkit/components/passwordmgr/test/unit/test_getPasswordFields.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e293c1aa1c10d38b271b48742650d97a4ee5061e", "parents": ["a15e503db4d1d7261680fb497af39b65babff013"], "tags": []}], "date": 1485992863, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "mozilla@noorenberghe.ca"}, "6863": {"changesets": [{"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1124604 - Move code for getting the outer window id into its own method. r=ato, a=test-only\n\nThere are several places which make use of DOMWindowUtils to determine the\nouter window id. Lets centralize it to a single method to avoid duplication.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1IRKMpBPFH", "files": ["testing/marionette/driver.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ef49463c6eb5c3db39bec41cefd5d861e3a44b4f", "parents": ["e293c1aa1c10d38b271b48742650d97a4ee5061e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1124604 - Add `focus` parameter to switch_to_window(). r=ato, a=test-only\n\nTo be able to run tests for backgrounds tabs, and to stay in compatibility\nwith switch_to_frame(), switch_to_window() has to support the `focus` parameter.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: YGPJisiI2i", "files": ["testing/marionette/browser.js", "testing/marionette/client/marionette_driver/marionette.py", "testing/marionette/driver.js", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_switch_window_chrome.py", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_switch_window_content.py", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_window_handles_chrome.py", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_window_handles_content.py", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_window_management.py", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_window_switching.py", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/unit-tests.ini", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/www/windowHandles.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9bbd592018080b2ef652e8575c848a5f505649c1", "parents": ["ef49463c6eb5c3db39bec41cefd5d861e3a44b4f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabor Krizsanits \u003cgkrizsanits@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1211098 - Fixing race from tab closing. r=gijs, a=test-only", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser_bug562649.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "069f770273c67eb42fd0b618b40fcb25f33cba38", "parents": ["9bbd592018080b2ef652e8575c848a5f505649c1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kate McKinley \u003ckmckinley@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335134 - Pref security.mixed_content.send_hsts_priming to false. r=mayhemer, a=lizzard", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "04c9d97c4cd7eec830c94d7493b7f42342e73e55", "parents": ["069f770273c67eb42fd0b618b40fcb25f33cba38"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1330593 part 1 - Allow non-flat external strings. r=jwalden, r=bz, a=jcristau", "files": ["js/public/Class.h", "js/src/builtin/TestingFunctions.cpp", "js/src/jit-test/tests/basic/external-strings.js", "js/src/jit/VMFunctions.cpp", "js/src/jsapi-tests/testExternalStrings.cpp", "js/src/vm/String-inl.h", "js/src/vm/String.cpp", "js/src/vm/String.h", "js/xpconnect/src/XPCString.cpp", "js/xpconnect/src/xpcpublic.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "87b26c2d0b93be6944b14bb972b8bb488887ac41", "parents": ["04c9d97c4cd7eec830c94d7493b7f42342e73e55"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Henning \u003cjh+bugzilla@buttercookie.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1333567 - Send the notification expected by the session store when restarting, too. r=sebastian, a=jcristau\n\nSince bug 1228593, the mobile session store\n- once again flushes its data when we are quitting, to make sure the latest state (including any potential cleaning of history/tabs) is flushed to disk\n- ignores windows/tabs closing as a byproduct of shutdown\n\nThe latter point is dependent on a new shutdown notification introduced in that bug. Because we forgot to add that notification to the restart code used for add-on updates, in that case the session store currently doesn't enter shutdown mode and therefore records the window being closed during shutdown before flushing its data to disk, which means that all open tabs are lost.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LgtdQoYwacM", "files": ["mobile/android/chrome/content/browser.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "eaaf5c7cf8ecc8e7855091e40ec91ef032416e6e", "parents": ["87b26c2d0b93be6944b14bb972b8bb488887ac41"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335365 - Add telemetry to see if we can remove moz-only XHR.reponseType. r=smaug, data-review=bsmedberg, a=jcristau", "files": ["dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestMainThread.cpp", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8f077c42aed8e4cd8fab03ecfbd2b0833bc66557", "parents": ["eaaf5c7cf8ecc8e7855091e40ec91ef032416e6e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ben Kelly \u003cben@wanderview.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335414 - Make ServiceWorkerManager::CreateNewRegistration() safer. r=asuth, a=ritu", "files": ["dom/workers/ServiceWorkerManager.cpp", "dom/workers/ServiceWorkerManager.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "933c8878910eb265fab7395692ede33c76bbb807", "parents": ["8f077c42aed8e4cd8fab03ecfbd2b0833bc66557"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1319370 - HTMLInputElement should select the directory for the FilePicker using the input type (file or directory). r=jwatt, a=jcristau", "files": ["dom/filesystem/Directory.h", "dom/html/HTMLInputElement.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "227c1ff7e0fa34989e80b0728c740a6d9d94f7b6", "parents": ["933c8878910eb265fab7395692ede33c76bbb807"], "tags": []}], "date": 1485993511, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6864": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 87b26c2d0b93 (bug 1330593) for bustage.", "files": ["js/public/Class.h", "js/src/builtin/TestingFunctions.cpp", "js/src/jit-test/tests/basic/external-strings.js", "js/src/jit/VMFunctions.cpp", "js/src/jsapi-tests/testExternalStrings.cpp", "js/src/vm/String-inl.h", "js/src/vm/String.cpp", "js/src/vm/String.h", "js/xpconnect/src/XPCString.cpp", "js/xpconnect/src/xpcpublic.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ec8f0f613a8c0c0470bfea9788a39e7fea9a53d5", "parents": ["227c1ff7e0fa34989e80b0728c740a6d9d94f7b6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1330593 part 1 - Allow non-flat external strings. r=jwalden, r=bz, a=jcristau", "files": ["js/public/Class.h", "js/src/builtin/TestingFunctions.cpp", "js/src/jit-test/tests/basic/external-strings.js", "js/src/jit/VMFunctions.cpp", "js/src/jsapi-tests/testExternalStrings.cpp", "js/src/vm/String-inl.h", "js/src/vm/String.cpp", "js/src/vm/String.h", "js/xpconnect/src/XPCString.cpp", "js/xpconnect/src/xpcpublic.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "93b639dcd0c2c6231932bdd8279dc858f6596bf6", "parents": ["ec8f0f613a8c0c0470bfea9788a39e7fea9a53d5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1485994099, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6865": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ben Kelly \u003cben@wanderview.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335425 Improve ScriptLoader CacheCreator's ability to handle failures and cancelation. r=baku a=jcristau", "files": ["dom/workers/ScriptLoader.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a243cd4ce4480144c8c605f57ca54e0aaa1dcf7a", "parents": ["93b639dcd0c2c6231932bdd8279dc858f6596bf6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ben Kelly \u003cben@wanderview.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334677 Make PostMessageRunnable handle the port being cycle collected. r=baku a=jcristau", "files": ["dom/messagechannel/MessagePort.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "339082e4a33aa237def532c990aaab2b5a4b5723", "parents": ["a243cd4ce4480144c8c605f57ca54e0aaa1dcf7a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486044739, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "bkelly@mozilla.com"}, "6866": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrzej Hunt \u003cahunt@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1120441 - Don't try to show tab-history panel if app has been shutdown. r=sebastian, a=ritu a=jcristau\n\nShowing the tab history panel involves a gecko call to retrieve tab history. This\ncan be slow, meaning we have no idea what state the app will be in when the tab\nhistory data is returned. Thus we need to protect the code that shows the tab\nhistory fragment against a number of scenarios to avoid crashes in those cases\nwhere the app might be shutting down:\n\n1. If onSaveInstanceState() has been called (which might happen before or after onPause(),\n   and might be linked to app shutdown - but the docs don't appear to give any guarantees),\n   fragment transactions cannot be performed. We protect against this by accepting loss\n   of state in fragment transactions.\n2. If the Activity has been completely destroyed, trying to perform a fragment transaction\n   will likewise fail. We protect against this by not even trying to perform the transaction\n   if we definitively know that the Activity is being shut down (ie isFinishing()).\n\nIn both of these cases, we simply must accept that we're potentially losing UI state: i.e.\na user could request the tab history panel via long-back-press, followed by exiting the app;\nwe now end up never ever showing the panel. This scenario doesn't seem like a major loss - and\nfixing this issue properly would require significant investment (i.e. we would need to either\ncache tab history on frontend side, or cache the tab-history panel request - and it's not clear\nusers will still care about seeing the panel the next time they open firefox).\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JsAK1By8yqn", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/BrowserApp.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/tabs/TabHistoryFragment.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "790848ae6b7fd673f9c8c3431b7011e01809eeb8", "parents": ["339082e4a33aa237def532c990aaab2b5a4b5723"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dimitry Andric \u003cdimitry\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1329520 - Fix \"memory/mozalloc/throw_gcc.h:35:1: note: declaration missing '[[noreturn]]' (libc++ 4.0)\" r=nfroyd a=jcristau", "files": ["memory/mozalloc/throw_gcc.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "87b018eade4650f4185910e364eeae7a9785649b", "parents": ["790848ae6b7fd673f9c8c3431b7011e01809eeb8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334201 - Ignore window.opener for insecure form warnings. r=MattN a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BLuwIAWEYHi", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/general/browser.ini", "browser/base/content/test/general/browser_insecureLoginForms.js", "browser/base/content/test/general/insecure_opener.html", "toolkit/components/passwordmgr/InsecurePasswordUtils.jsm", "toolkit/components/passwordmgr/LoginManagerContent.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "80636f3bf46c7cccacb0f3e4422a7344fa80b6e6", "parents": ["87b018eade4650f4185910e364eeae7a9785649b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334774 - re-introduce the hostname into ssl error messages, r=nhnt11 a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CexcCq5qo1v", "files": ["browser/base/content/aboutNetError.xhtml", "browser/base/content/test/general/browser_aboutCertError.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "166a10fe355f19efa0d0009b7ccbced38ec24bb2", "parents": ["80636f3bf46c7cccacb0f3e4422a7344fa80b6e6"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486051406, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6867": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrew Sutherland \u003casutherland@asutherland.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1319531 - Ensure all streams provided by DatabaseFile can be read without generating NS_BASE_STREAM_WOULD_BLOCK errors. beta52 version. r=janv a=jcristau\n\nbeta 52 patch changes:\n- minor bit-rot in context\n- test had to be devolved to use old-style generators and relevant idioms\n\nIndexedDB database operations are written such that they must execute\nsynchronously. For this reason, the add/put operation reads/writes its\nBlobs to disk in a synchronous fashion. However, with the introduction\nof SendStream-backed Blobs for large (\u003e1 MiB) blobs whose contents are\nstreamed to the parent replacing nsStringInputStream-backed Blobs\n(whose contents were sent up in a single IPC message that might exceed\nthe size limit and cause a crash), this has no longer been a safe\nassumption. However, the problems weren't immediately obvious because\nmost pre-WASM Blobs are smaller than the 1MiB threshold and even when\nthey exceeded the size, their memory-backed contents could rapidly be\nsent to the parent via IPC, making NS_BASE_STREAM_WOULD_BLOCK errors\nrare/hard to reproduce. (rr and its enforced single-threading is a\ngood way to reproduce, however. Also, see the testing patch on the\nbug that introduces artificial delays into SendStream.)\n\nIncluded SpecialPowersObserver.jsm minor changes to \"CreateFiles\":\n- appendRelativePath is used instead of appendPath because appendPath\nonly allows a single path component to be appended. In other words,\nfile creation is limited to files at the root of the profile\ndirectory using appendPath, which is needlessly limiting.\n- outStream is now closed even if no data is provided. This is\nessential on windows where file deletion only occurs when all handles\nare closed. Without this fix, \"RemoveFiles\" side-effect of deleting\nthe created files might not take effect until garbage collection runs\nand collects the outStream.", "files": ["dom/indexedDB/ActorsParent.cpp", "dom/indexedDB/test/helpers.js", "dom/indexedDB/test/mochitest.ini", "dom/indexedDB/test/test_file_put_deleted.html", "testing/specialpowers/content/SpecialPowersObserver.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4a6fa0969049899d50f0beea768bcd7c6a715b5b", "parents": ["166a10fe355f19efa0d0009b7ccbced38ec24bb2"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486051581, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6868": {"changesets": [{"author": "Rail Aliiev \u003crail@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334538 - Do not update SHA1 bouncer aliases in Firefox 52. r=jlorenzo a=release DONTBUILD\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GcObzm1nzlP", "files": ["testing/mozharness/configs/releases/bouncer_firefox_esr.py", "testing/mozharness/configs/releases/bouncer_firefox_release.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f3bc1ad9fc3c91b5d1dd6e21daa080628250b1d9", "parents": ["4a6fa0969049899d50f0beea768bcd7c6a715b5b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486051729, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "raliiev@mozilla.com"}, "6869": {"changesets": [{"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1307461 - Disable MediaPipelineTest.TestAudioSendNoMux. r=jesup, a=test-only", "files": ["media/webrtc/signaling/test/mediapipeline_unittest.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1ad9c3c00e7d80da334596bfeb48641e7c118ad6", "parents": ["f3bc1ad9fc3c91b5d1dd6e21daa080628250b1d9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Yura Zenevich \u003cyzenevich@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1322593 - Add match function for text change checker to stricten match based on modified text. r=tbsaunde, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 44LEulhW671", "files": ["accessible/tests/mochitest/events.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f72072777689bd6b37da3410699829090c146cb4", "parents": ["1ad9c3c00e7d80da334596bfeb48641e7c118ad6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Trevor Saunders \u003ctbsaunde@tbsaunde.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1322593 - Avoid merging text change events for unrelated accessibles. r=davidb, a=jcristau", "files": ["accessible/base/NotificationController.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8336a9d40a9a93ce81b4d47aff16c61c19bfe4c9", "parents": ["f72072777689bd6b37da3410699829090c146cb4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Trevor Saunders \u003ctbsaunde@tbsaunde.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1322593 - Don't coalesce non contiguous text changes under the same accessible. r=davidb, a=jcristau", "files": ["accessible/base/NotificationController.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "61c451adc3b17e54853d4fe6a68045ed6e171414", "parents": ["8336a9d40a9a93ce81b4d47aff16c61c19bfe4c9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Trevor Saunders \u003ctbsaunde@tbsaunde.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1322593 - Allow asynchronous checking of text change events. r=yzen, a=jcristau\n\nThis allows us to check for multiple text change events that could come in any order.", "files": ["accessible/tests/mochitest/events.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d52e2bceab57d08544a310ef88ab4ca504238f72", "parents": ["61c451adc3b17e54853d4fe6a68045ed6e171414"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Trevor Saunders \u003ctbsaunde@tbsaunde.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1322593 - Test that unrelated text change events are not coalesced. r=yzen, a=jcristau", "files": ["accessible/tests/mochitest/events/a11y.ini", "accessible/tests/mochitest/events/test_bug1322593.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5ec5c9a7719b756bf831b11c76c6467a2b0fd45e", "parents": ["d52e2bceab57d08544a310ef88ab4ca504238f72"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Trevor Saunders \u003ctbsaunde@tbsaunde.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1322593 - Add test for multiple independent text changes under the same accessible. r=yzen, a=jcristau", "files": ["accessible/tests/mochitest/events/a11y.ini", "accessible/tests/mochitest/events/test_bug1322593-2.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d171c36d484800b1bb00db1612460a7120dd2fdf", "parents": ["5ec5c9a7719b756bf831b11c76c6467a2b0fd45e"], "tags": ["FIREFOX_52_0b3_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_52_0b3_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1486059252, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6870": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 790848ae6b7f (bug 1120441) for Android bustage.", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/BrowserApp.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/tabs/TabHistoryFragment.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1a6c3c479c469f83cfe12e0e12b6f9f296665b4f", "parents": ["d171c36d484800b1bb00db1612460a7120dd2fdf"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486059429, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6871": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrzej Hunt \u003cahunt@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1120441 - Don't try to show tab-history panel if app has been shutdown. r=sebastian, a=jcristau\n\nShowing the tab history panel involves a gecko call to retrieve tab history. This\ncan be slow, meaning we have no idea what state the app will be in when the tab\nhistory data is returned. Thus we need to protect the code that shows the tab\nhistory fragment against a number of scenarios to avoid crashes in those cases\nwhere the app might be shutting down:\n\n1. If onSaveInstanceState() has been called (which might happen before or after onPause(),\n   and might be linked to app shutdown - but the docs don't appear to give any guarantees),\n   fragment transactions cannot be performed. We protect against this by accepting loss\n   of state in fragment transactions.\n2. If the Activity has been completely destroyed, trying to perform a fragment transaction\n   will likewise fail. We protect against this by not even trying to perform the transaction\n   if we definitively know that the Activity is being shut down (ie isFinishing()).\n\nIn both of these cases, we simply must accept that we're potentially losing UI state: i.e.\na user could request the tab history panel via long-back-press, followed by exiting the app;\nwe now end up never ever showing the panel. This scenario doesn't seem like a major loss - and\nfixing this issue properly would require significant investment (i.e. we would need to either\ncache tab history on frontend side, or cache the tab-history panel request - and it's not clear\nusers will still care about seeing the panel the next time they open firefox).\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JsAK1By8yqn", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/BrowserApp.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/tabs/TabHistoryFragment.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3b07081139babab5746944d9e9356160f978ab4c", "parents": ["1a6c3c479c469f83cfe12e0e12b6f9f296665b4f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486062334, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6872": {"changesets": [{"author": "Geoff Brown \u003cgbrown@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335944 - Delay devicemanagerADB sdk check until connect() time. r=bc, a=test-only", "files": ["testing/mozbase/mozdevice/mozdevice/devicemanagerADB.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d3dcda2046c2b138522b4d07288ab4260a6f3e46", "parents": ["3b07081139babab5746944d9e9356160f978ab4c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1303298 - Use BrowserTestUtils.waitForErrorPage to wait for certerror page load. r=nhnt11, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BzT1cQAd9Qx", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/general/browser_mixed_content_cert_override.js", "browser/base/content/test/general/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "757ad211356f4f91e4d8129c086e3018ecbd1460", "parents": ["d3dcda2046c2b138522b4d07288ab4260a6f3e46"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Boris Zbarsky \u003cbzbarsky@mit.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1323324 tests. r=till, a=test-only", "files": ["dom/bindings/test/TestFunctions.cpp", "dom/bindings/test/TestFunctions.h", "dom/promise/tests/chrome.ini", "dom/promise/tests/file_promise_argument_tests.js", "dom/promise/tests/mochitest.ini", "dom/promise/tests/test_promise_argument.html", "dom/promise/tests/test_promise_argument_xrays.html", "dom/promise/tests/test_promise_callback_retval.html", "dom/webidl/TestFunctions.webidl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ff8566df88d5323305cc1592af072957e4ee1f34", "parents": ["757ad211356f4f91e4d8129c086e3018ecbd1460"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Boris Zbarsky \u003cbzbarsky@mit.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334537 - Make sure to clear out our external string cache if the length doesn't match, since our length no longer needs to match our stringbuffer. r=froydnj, a=lizzard\n\nWithout this change, we could do a \"short\" get of a string (e.g. from\nXMLHttpRequest), then do another get that returns the same stringbuffer but a\nlonger length.  But we wouldn't notice, hit our cache, and return the same,\ntoo-short, external string.  The site would not see the new data it should have\nseen.", "files": ["dom/bindings/test/TestFunctions.cpp", "dom/bindings/test/TestFunctions.h", "dom/bindings/test/mochitest.ini", "dom/bindings/test/test_stringBindings.html", "dom/webidl/TestFunctions.webidl", "js/xpconnect/src/XPCString.cpp", "js/xpconnect/src/xpcpublic.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b9e7643b8be64976276573389670f70d57e1fe9f", "parents": ["ff8566df88d5323305cc1592af072957e4ee1f34"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486081459, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6873": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Revert the newly-added tests from rev ff8566df88d5. a=test-only", "files": ["dom/promise/tests/chrome.ini", "dom/promise/tests/file_promise_argument_tests.js", "dom/promise/tests/mochitest.ini", "dom/promise/tests/test_promise_argument.html", "dom/promise/tests/test_promise_argument_xrays.html", "dom/promise/tests/test_promise_callback_retval.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9759594e223f25075dde334fe96af323bf33d144", "parents": ["b9e7643b8be64976276573389670f70d57e1fe9f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486082273, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6874": {"changesets": [{"author": "Paul Adenot \u003cpaul@paul.cx\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1320705 - Add a test to check that decoding an Opus file does to produce a long tail. r=jya a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: B4IlW1cWYlX", "files": ["dom/media/webaudio/test/mochitest.ini", "dom/media/webaudio/test/sweep-300-330-1sec.opus", "dom/media/webaudio/test/test_decodeOpusTail.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "777a6e437a68ec51296c16ed6f8a8d409ab22480", "parents": ["9759594e223f25075dde334fe96af323bf33d144"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486127383, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "paul@paul.cx"}, "6875": {"changesets": [{"author": "Masatoshi Kimura \u003cVYV03354@nifty.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1327960 - Don't escape the query part of nsSimpleURI. r=valentin.gosu, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: G5Shb8kYYTx", "files": ["dom/url/tests/test_url.html", "netwerk/base/nsSimpleURI.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7b850284e545fdd6a70003adcb3cdc1f6ee76a3e", "parents": ["777a6e437a68ec51296c16ed6f8a8d409ab22480"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Paul Adenot \u003cpaul@paul.cx\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1331869 - Uplift a double-free fix (cubeb revision f82f15). a=jcristau", "files": ["media/libcubeb/prevent-double-free.patch", "media/libcubeb/src/cubeb_wasapi.cpp", "media/libcubeb/update.sh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a5045a32c413753551a2f532c76d035cfc09623c", "parents": ["7b850284e545fdd6a70003adcb3cdc1f6ee76a3e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matthew Noorenberghe \u003cmozilla@noorenberghe.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334026 - Show the the insecure field warning on insecure password fields even if they're not marked. r=mconley, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LxvPzD3SOnc", "files": ["toolkit/components/satchel/nsFormFillController.cpp", "toolkit/components/satchel/test/test_password_autocomplete.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cb874e871110d67e78f2c8bc37b618ebb9ba0e4c", "parents": ["a5045a32c413753551a2f532c76d035cfc09623c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486136405, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6876": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003crelease@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Automatic version bump. CLOSED TREE NO BUG a=release", "files": ["browser/config/version_display.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8ce35c6b23a09774533df99b771afe7c93603887", "parents": ["cb874e871110d67e78f2c8bc37b618ebb9ba0e4c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "ffxbld \u003crelease@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging d171c36d484800b1bb00db1612460a7120dd2fdf with FIREFOX_52_0b3_BUILD1, FIREFOX_52_0b3_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ff56de0ee8dc01c99e4919b626f8a3c339aca01f", "parents": ["8ce35c6b23a09774533df99b771afe7c93603887"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486137421, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "6877": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out 3 changesets (bug 1322277) for causing bug 1334149.\n\nBacked out changeset 7ce8d1a5678c (bug 1322277)\nBacked out changeset 96e2a1ec523d (bug 1322277)\nBacked out changeset 6f4c97200bb7 (bug 1322277)", "files": ["testing/marionette/client/marionette_driver/marionette.py", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/runner/base.py", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_capabilities.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2e4f262fdaa6ca832c5e731c914db512feadc803", "parents": ["ff56de0ee8dc01c99e4919b626f8a3c339aca01f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Geoff Brown \u003cgbrown@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335501 - Trigger test job retry when Android devicemanager _runCmd() times out. r=jmaher, a=test-only", "files": ["testing/mozharness/mozharness/mozilla/testing/errors.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0b69d8923c19e9ee020aae9e865bc22cb111853f", "parents": ["2e4f262fdaa6ca832c5e731c914db512feadc803"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1313271 - Wait for load in browser_html_tooltip_hover. r=rickychien, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9CHkXMtwTrG", "files": ["devtools/client/shared/test/browser_html_tooltip_hover.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "378fdaee41fb7c05379eb7298e414d50d5e6f6ca", "parents": ["0b69d8923c19e9ee020aae9e865bc22cb111853f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Felipe Gomes \u003cfelipc@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1282484 - Add a mechanism to control plugin fallback content. r=qDot, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Lt4tOdFdQzN\n* * *\nBug 1282484 - Cache the value of PreferFallback() because ShouldPlay() is called several times during the load process. r=qDot\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DqjCHssaJde\n* * *\nBug 1282484 - Write structure for pref-configurable fallback rules list, and include initial set of rules. r=qDot\n* * *\nBug 1282485 - Plugin fallback rule - don't use fallback when the descendant has an embed element\n* * *\nBug 1316102 - Plugin fallback rule - use fallback when it contains a \u003cvideo\u003e element\n* * *\nBug 1282487 - Plugin fallback rule - don't use fallback when it contains links to adobe.com\n* * *\nBug 1282486 - Plugin fallback rule - don't use fallback when it contains 'install Flash' instructions\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DexVBrAfaTb", "files": ["dom/base/nsObjectLoadingContent.cpp", "dom/base/nsObjectLoadingContent.h", "modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "51e2150d6f00f343a161687dbf0c038f3c707ad0", "parents": ["378fdaee41fb7c05379eb7298e414d50d5e6f6ca"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tomer Cohen \u003ctomer@tomercohen.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1332625 - about:support on Android should not link to about:profiles (broken link). r=standard8, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4OEyNMJXg6m", "files": ["toolkit/content/aboutSupport.xhtml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "72b706bd282d698bc759e6ff675a16305fe399d3", "parents": ["51e2150d6f00f343a161687dbf0c038f3c707ad0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335451 - Tweak thumbnail placeholder colors and make placeholder letters uppercase. r=Gijs, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1s2MMPNBA5S", "files": ["browser/base/content/newtab/sites.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0d9d7517318f1ddf27dbadff64fa083de6da67bd", "parents": ["72b706bd282d698bc759e6ff675a16305fe399d3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1336072 - Avoid setting position:absolute on #newtab-grid since it breaks rearranging and deleting tiles. r=Gijs, a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FTbIP28uD5k", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/newtab/newTab.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "51523138a95eff972a01953746d86341ed1f402a", "parents": ["0d9d7517318f1ddf27dbadff64fa083de6da67bd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luke Wagner \u003cluke@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334239 - Baldr: fix and optimize call_indirect. r=bbouvier, a=lizzard", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/wasm/tables.js", "js/src/jit/MacroAssembler.h", "js/src/jit/arm/MacroAssembler-arm-inl.h", "js/src/jit/arm64/MacroAssembler-arm64-inl.h", "js/src/jit/mips-shared/MacroAssembler-mips-shared-inl.h", "js/src/jit/x86-shared/MacroAssembler-x86-shared-inl.h", "js/src/wasm/WasmFrameIterator.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmStubs.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmTypes.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e69d59dae7b2f34b56e7805974841953b04493bd", "parents": ["51523138a95eff972a01953746d86341ed1f402a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sebastian Kaspari \u003cs.kaspari@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1318667 - Do not use palette library on x86 devices (Use BitmapUtils.getDominantColor()). r=ahunt, a=sledru\n\nOur version of the palette support library crashes for certain icons on x86 systems.", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/icons/processing/ColorProcessor.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/util/HardwareUtils.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b8b67afeb8f18cffa2ae678ee9a6c2f572323441", "parents": ["e69d59dae7b2f34b56e7805974841953b04493bd"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486323796, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6878": {"changesets": [{"author": "Wes Kocher \u003cwkocher@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1336654 - Skip the suddenly permafailing tests a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1KLjbaojvYc", "files": ["dom/security/test/contentverifier/browser.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e5373fbb022e1a227116a989d22929040bfabc3c", "parents": ["b8b67afeb8f18cffa2ae678ee9a6c2f572323441"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486325274, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "philringnalda@gmail.com"}, "6879": {"changesets": [{"author": "Carsten \"Tomcat\" Book \u003ccbook@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset cb874e871110 (bug 1334026) on request because need to wait for a different bug/set of patches", "files": ["toolkit/components/satchel/nsFormFillController.cpp", "toolkit/components/satchel/test/test_password_autocomplete.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "06eda6a9a51fa6a6d2d2e38b178d4bf009891a77", "parents": ["e5373fbb022e1a227116a989d22929040bfabc3c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486375282, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6880": {"changesets": [{"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1318265 - NativeKey shouldn't handle messages when mWidget has already been destroyed r=m_kato a=jcristau\n\nWhen mWidget was already destroyed, anybody shouldn't dispatch WidgetEvent on it. Therefore, NativeKey::InitKeyEvent() has MOZ_CRASH() for detecting such dangerous bug and some users hit it.\n\nEach message handler of NativeKey should check if mWidget has already gone.\n\nIdeally, nsWindow shouldn't create NativeKey and try to handle the message with it. However, using NativeKey's message handlers can put some information to the log. Therefore, this patch doesn't touch nsWindow.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4k5VfaKHPgG", "files": ["widget/windows/KeyboardLayout.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "afe0d94be5473f11a871efad31bb638c17ca3e8f", "parents": ["06eda6a9a51fa6a6d2d2e38b178d4bf009891a77"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thomas Wisniewski \u003cwisniewskit@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1319744 - Ensure that progress events and corresponding LOADING readystatechanges fire as per spec. r=baku a=jcristau", "files": ["dom/workers/test/bug1063538_worker.js", "dom/workers/test/mochitest.ini", "dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestMainThread.cpp", "testing/web-platform/meta/progress-events/tests/submissions/Samsung/firing-events-http-no-content-length.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/tests/XMLHttpRequest/resources/xmlhttprequest-event-order.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "462a50df3d934aaff8483f9aa0f6a231d91f6cae", "parents": ["afe0d94be5473f11a871efad31bb638c17ca3e8f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alexandre Poirot \u003cpoirot.alex@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1328004 - Fix race when closing the devtools while a previous instance is still loading. r=jryans a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2a58l4DjCtv", "files": ["devtools/client/framework/devtools-browser.js", "devtools/client/framework/devtools.js", "devtools/client/framework/test/browser.ini", "devtools/client/framework/test/browser_toolbox_races.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9a1b79873db7526a0c9f33511e224a617af7ca6b", "parents": ["462a50df3d934aaff8483f9aa0f6a231d91f6cae"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486394491, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6881": {"changesets": [{"author": "Liang-Heng Chen \u003cxeonchen@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1328106 - check IPC state before sending event; r=jdm a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CeWCIG0dyKS", "files": ["dom/network/TCPSocketParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a9ed733f547b0438f8ca6ef4bc7be8dd8fdc520c", "parents": ["9a1b79873db7526a0c9f33511e224a617af7ca6b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "kvark \u003ckvark@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1330672 - Fix for the YCbCr blit origin. r=jgilbert a=jcristau", "files": ["gfx/gl/GLBlitHelper.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f367195ced0f4b16e38bd350885c701f5972a9f7", "parents": ["a9ed733f547b0438f8ca6ef4bc7be8dd8fdc520c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1331939 - Rename GlobalFlags to GlobalTypeImmediate to fix MinGW build. r=luke, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1jXd3LUZ0dT", "files": ["js/src/wasm/WasmBinaryConstants.h", "js/src/wasm/WasmTextToBinary.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmValidate.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b42c3703393d1d9192066cb68c136e6189ee437d", "parents": ["f367195ced0f4b16e38bd350885c701f5972a9f7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Morris Tseng \u003cmtseng@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1332798 - Add null check after CreateIOSurface. r=mstange a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6JIR8y04cXm", "files": ["widget/cocoa/RectTextureImage.mm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cfa727a93b0bd874cf02dd6fd58c0a0353b52105", "parents": ["b42c3703393d1d9192066cb68c136e6189ee437d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Valentin Gosu \u003cvalentin.gosu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334520 - Trigger captive portal recheck recheck for NS_NETWORK_LINK_DATA_CHANGED events r=mcmanus a=jcristau\nMozReview-Commit-ID: L8XBLx88PbS", "files": ["netwerk/base/nsIOService.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "35b9c31fbd27ef69f59d41c930040053b2240430", "parents": ["cfa727a93b0bd874cf02dd6fd58c0a0353b52105"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ben Kelly \u003cben@wanderview.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1336529 - Handle ServiceWorkerInfo destruction while released KeepAliveToken. r=asuth a=jcristau", "files": ["dom/workers/ServiceWorkerManager.cpp", "dom/workers/ServiceWorkerPrivate.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cb083bb2dd7d75721602bb2768f6f8e096d910f4", "parents": ["35b9c31fbd27ef69f59d41c930040053b2240430"], "tags": []}, {"author": "J.C. Jones \u003cjjones@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335466 - Regenerate the CA RootHashes.inc r=keeler a=jcristau\n\nThis is a maintenance re-run since Firefox 50, to include new roots.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HSs2P6S65A7", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/RootHashes.inc", "security/manager/tools/KnownRootHashes.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6868ec86bd38a3ab399903863436d7c90d037cef", "parents": ["cb083bb2dd7d75721602bb2768f6f8e096d910f4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nathan Froyd \u003cfroydnj@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335460 - Release globals properly when GetFilesHelper is destroyed on the main thread. r=smaug, a=jcristau", "files": ["dom/filesystem/GetFilesHelper.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cc219ce6b182fef7493409735c6be3e463fde90f", "parents": ["6868ec86bd38a3ab399903863436d7c90d037cef"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486396216, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6882": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1331939 - Rename two other instances of GlobalFlags. a=bustage", "files": ["js/src/wasm/WasmBinaryFormat.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f78e406f5ef5cf13522b70e981561b1280dc917a", "parents": ["cc219ce6b182fef7493409735c6be3e463fde90f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486400499, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6883": {"changesets": [{"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset f78e406f5ef5 and b42c3703393d (bug 1331939) for landing on the wrong branch. r=backout a=backout", "files": ["js/src/wasm/WasmBinaryConstants.h", "js/src/wasm/WasmBinaryFormat.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmTextToBinary.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmValidate.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ecec7302f40ddd26c5f3c6cb48eac35b8977d772", "parents": ["f78e406f5ef5cf13522b70e981561b1280dc917a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Georg Koppen \u003cgk@torproject.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1331939 - Rename GlobalFlags to GlobalTypeImmediate to fix MinGW build. r=luke, a=jcristau", "files": ["js/src/wasm/WasmBinaryConstants.h", "js/src/wasm/WasmBinaryFormat.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmTextToBinary.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c48c37867d35fb2ffc8457834e12192a799d020c", "parents": ["ecec7302f40ddd26c5f3c6cb48eac35b8977d772"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486402720, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "6884": {"changesets": [{"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334947 - Treat a keydown event as inputting empty text if following char message has gone and gets WM_NULL message at calling PeekMessage() for removing a found char message. r=m_kato, a=jcristau\n\nThere are still a lot of crash due to failing to get following WM_CHAR message.  Almost half of them are, we found a WM_CHAR message but it's gone at removing the message from the queue.\n\nAlthough, we're still not sure what happen actually.  It could be possible if somebody hooks PeekMessage() or something.  Then, we can assume that the found message isn't necessary for the user because it must be removed by somebody when it became unnecessary or is handled.\n\nThis patch mark a new bool flag, mCharMessageHasGone, as true in such case.  Then, NativeKey will dispatch keypress events without following char messages and mark the event as consumed.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: mporX1sihC", "files": ["widget/windows/KeyboardLayout.cpp", "widget/windows/KeyboardLayout.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "82cbddf41c09e4031f31ca6541374d8f6283e82f", "parents": ["c48c37867d35fb2ffc8457834e12192a799d020c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486404162, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6885": {"changesets": [{"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335670 - NativeKey should dispatch consumed keydown event when it receives WM_NULL at removing WM_*CHAR from the queue and the original message has gone. r=m_kato, a=jcristau\n\nCurrently, NativeKey::GetFollowingCharMessage() tries 5 times to remove found char message from the queue.  It was enough when we found this issue at developing Metrofox.\n\nHowever, this hack is not enough for some odd keyboard layouts because we see some crash reports which gives up to remove a char message from the queue because 5 WM_NULL messages are returned.\n\nFor preventing this crash, we should check if there is the message which is trying to remove from the queue when NativeKey receives WM_NULL.  Then, when there is no key message in the queue or next key message becomes non-char message,, NativeKey should dispatch consumed keydown event because we can assume that the key operation may have already been handled or canceled.  Otherwise, NativeKey should retry to remove the message again (until 50 times!, it's just enough big magic number, there is no concrete reason).\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1c6Y4OoQdrP", "files": ["widget/windows/KeyboardLayout.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fc4e87e2dcd5477f45b5df26ad937b0e85afa7a4", "parents": ["82cbddf41c09e4031f31ca6541374d8f6283e82f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1336028 - NativeKey::GetFollowingCharMessage() should take newer char message when found char message and removed message from the queue is different but their scancode indicates same physical key r=m_kato, a=jcristau\n\nNativeKey::GetFollowingCharMessage() may remove a char message which is different from previously found message in the queue because hacky keyboard layout or utility can overwrite the wParam when it's removed from the queue.\n\nNow, we should assume that newer message, i.e., actually removed from the queue, is the expected message by the user.  See bug 1336028 comment 0 for the actual scenarios which are collected by crash reports.\nhttps://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1336028#c0\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9ZgukHH1vfi", "files": ["widget/windows/KeyboardLayout.cpp", "widget/windows/KeyboardLayout.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c110e92591e2ed1713e1a78b2471b1a9a08a5bdb", "parents": ["fc4e87e2dcd5477f45b5df26ad937b0e85afa7a4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1336080 - When NativeKey::GetFollowingCharMessage() founds different message when it fails to remove a found char message, it should retry to remove the newly found message if it's caused by same physical key. r=m_kato, a=jcristau\n\nWhen NativeKey::GetFollowingCharMessage() tries to remove a char message from the queue, the message might be changed by odd keyboard layout or something.  In such case, if the new char message is also caused by same physical key, the char  message must be overwritten.  Then, we should take the new char message instead.\n\nNote that this patch saves original found char message into kFoundCharMsg and it's logged by each points for indicating if this case has occurred.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HAduq8sfwFt", "files": ["widget/windows/KeyboardLayout.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "add3eb9e5942ba027beba74c9bbc488554c31b7b", "parents": ["c110e92591e2ed1713e1a78b2471b1a9a08a5bdb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1336322 - NativeKey::GetFollowingCharMessage() should treat the char message has gone if PeekMessage() failed to remove found char message and next key message becomes non-char message or different key's char message. r=m_kato, a=jcristau\n\nThis patch depends on bug 1336080.\n\nWhen PeekMessage() fails to remove found char message, NativeKey::GetFollowingCharMessage() tries to check next key message in the queue again.  Then, when next key message becomes non-char message, such as WM_KEYDOWN or WM_KEYUP, the char message must be removed by odd keyboard layout or something.  Similarly, when next key message is a char message but it's caused by different key, the found char message must be removed by one of them too.\n\nSo, in these cases, NativeKey::GetFollowingCharMessage() should treat the key operation is already handled or canceled by the odd keyboard layout or somebody else.  Additionally, in the latter case, following char message should be handled as orphan char message(s) as usual.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8ahs8I0HUQ2", "files": ["widget/windows/KeyboardLayout.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "066a9139b0603a46e56a5df14d9d4ecfdabb7351", "parents": ["add3eb9e5942ba027beba74c9bbc488554c31b7b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1336331 - NativeKey::GetFollowingCharMessage() should try to use GetMessage() when PeekMessage() failed to remove a char message from the queue and there is still existing a char message. r=m_kato, a=jcristau\n\nI think that when PeekMessage(PM_REMOVE) failed to remove a char message but next key message is still a char message, it may be possible that the odd keyboard layout or utility hook only PeekMessage(PM_NOREMOVE) and GetMessage().  If so, we can explain what occurs in this case.\n\nI'm still not sure this fixes the case of bug 1336322 comment 0, but we should try to do this because I don't have better idea.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: CxoO24n167t", "files": ["widget/windows/KeyboardLayout.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "501a3fa83897af9598adfd6f794b5d5ea82fe237", "parents": ["066a9139b0603a46e56a5df14d9d4ecfdabb7351"], "tags": ["FIREFOX_52_0b4_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_52_0b4_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1486405092, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6886": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 900745 - Remove bogus fallback codepath. r=mattwoodrow a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GnGZFFRRTgE", "files": ["gfx/layers/ipc/CrossProcessCompositorBridgeParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dcdc85ecb2f31204d00686f88e8f452bf2526b65", "parents": ["501a3fa83897af9598adfd6f794b5d5ea82fe237"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486406064, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "kgupta@mozilla.com"}, "6887": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld", "branch": "MOBILE520b4_2017020616_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Automated checkin: version bump for fennec 52.0b4 release. DONTBUILD CLOSED TREE a=release", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a6eca0088a1eb0b743bec652eec1b77caeee9f6d", "parents": ["501a3fa83897af9598adfd6f794b5d5ea82fe237"], "tags": ["FENNEC_52_0b4_BUILD1", "FENNEC_52_0b4_RELEASE"]}, {"author": "ffxbld", "branch": "MOBILE520b4_2017020616_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Added FENNEC_52_0b4_RELEASE FENNEC_52_0b4_BUILD1 tag(s) for changeset a6eca0088a1e. DONTBUILD CLOSED TREE a=release", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2366c96300e9dcce051fb524253deac74cd2ee84", "parents": ["a6eca0088a1eb0b743bec652eec1b77caeee9f6d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1486418550, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "6888": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1320972 - Allow a max difference of 1 on Android for 722923-1.html. a=test-only", "files": ["layout/reftests/bugs/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dbca76cb3592ef8dd2f447b50c9b559b9d58bd7a", "parents": ["dcdc85ecb2f31204d00686f88e8f452bf2526b65"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hannes Verschore \u003chv1989@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1336448 - Disable helper thread logging in Tracelogger. r=bbouvier, a=jcristau", "files": ["js/src/vm/TraceLogging.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2f4590c268133d1b0fca526e4de04d16b7cabe5e", "parents": ["dbca76cb3592ef8dd2f447b50c9b559b9d58bd7a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "vincentliu \u003cvliu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1323122 - Update WebGL Conformance Test with html/js. r=jgilbert, a=jcristau\n\n---\n .../attribs/gl-bindAttribLocation-aliasing.html    |    2 +-\n .../attribs/gl-vertexattribpointer.html            |   23 +-\n .../conformance/buffers/buffer-uninitialized.html  |  123 +\n .../context/constants-and-properties.html          |   96 +-\n ...t-a