1ce69b8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335442 - Update wording of automigration notification bar and add tests. r=jaws, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EkuOQmRjqOF", "files": ["browser/components/migration/AutoMigrate.jsm", "browser/components/migration/content/extra-migration-strings.properties", "browser/components/migration/jar.mn", "browser/components/migration/tests/browser/browser.ini", "browser/components/migration/tests/browser/browser_undo_notification_wording.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "599e6b4f1e8ee922913213fdea17aed0f90f501f", "parents": ["120c8ec619d9b25c6388a104816da9959e4daa2d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "EKR \u003cekr@rtfm.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1331280 - Generic telemetry probe for TLS handshake status. r=keeler, a=jcristau", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.cpp", "security/pkix/include/pkix/pkixnss.h", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json", "toolkit/components/telemetry/histogram-whitelists.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8f90de47b3f224a548717df9375159218c3e6ac2", "parents": ["599e6b4f1e8ee922913213fdea17aed0f90f501f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335018 - Make the side identity popup adhere to role=alertdialog for a11y. r=Gijs, r=MarcoZ, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DpqeeN570H9", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/components/controlcenter/content/panel.inc.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "85a6f67ca811d4a3d9a4136a3216b17fd0f92acf", "parents": ["8f90de47b3f224a548717df9375159218c3e6ac2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Micha\u0142 G\u00f3rny \u003cmgorny@gentoo.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1329798 - Include sys/sysmacros.h for major(), minor() on Linux. r=glandium, a=jcristau\n\nInclude sys/sysmacros.h explicitly as that will be required by future\nglibc versions to expose major() and minor() macros.\n\nBug: https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1329798", "files": ["config/system-headers", "xpcom/io/nsLocalFileUnix.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5326967d9271ae3f45dd19890de854e767b9dde7", "parents": ["85a6f67ca811d4a3d9a4136a3216b17fd0f92acf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ting-Yu Lin \u003ctlin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1339797 - Fix select-all events fired by touch incorrectly hide the carets. r=mtseng, a=jcristau\n\nsHideCaretsForMouseInput is default to true on all platforms. When clicking\n\"SELECT ALL\" on Fennec toolbar in \u003cinput\u003e, AccessibleCaretManager will\nreceive SELECTALL_REASON with MOZ_SOURCE_TOUCH.\n\nWe should hide the carets only if the select-all reason is fired by\nkeyboard, not by touch.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: D7FYIH5ZGS0", "files": ["layout/base/AccessibleCaretManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "396f58f0d63c4d05aa7c59c4e13b1d6b02e77e1b", "parents": ["5326967d9271ae3f45dd19890de854e767b9dde7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Honza Bambas \u003chonzab.moz@firemni.cz\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1326136 - Let nsHttpConnection close it's transaction on shutdown. r=mcmanus, a=jcristau", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpConnection.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpConnection.h", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpConnectionMgr.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "021a342af91fe0933e1877695ebe186509e30274", "parents": ["396f58f0d63c4d05aa7c59c4e13b1d6b02e77e1b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Pearson \u003cjames-p@moving-picture.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1333720 - Support Unknown/Unsupported widget type 13 and 17. r=karlt, a=jcristau", "files": ["widget/gtk/gtk2drawing.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3434e8e52c3f7725aabc237a9eb893058694fbe3", "parents": ["021a342af91fe0933e1877695ebe186509e30274"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1340735 - Terminate process when failing to attach it to job group. r=mhowell, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BVCPRFH6TV2", "files": ["toolkit/modules/subprocess/subprocess_worker_win.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8173156d60e0aaa2abf4da543fdf61c03f240a75", "parents": ["3434e8e52c3f7725aabc237a9eb893058694fbe3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1339509 - Map ISO_Left_Tab to DOM Tab key. r=karlt, a=jcristau\n\nShift + Tab key combination causes ISO_Left_Tab keysym instead of Tab.  It should be mapped to DOM Tab key.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: IgQj7tkQdoJ", "files": ["widget/NativeKeyToDOMKeyName.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "732a5221be43ac411b14b77dc4a686ac812fb495", "parents": ["8173156d60e0aaa2abf4da543fdf61c03f240a75"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 410857 - Part 1: Traverse overflow lines too so we don't miss some text. r=jfkthame, a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/base/nsBidiPresUtils.cpp", "layout/generic/nsBlockFrame.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4619a89b7f733e17ed7968bc7cdbcecdaaf6c9f5", "parents": ["732a5221be43ac411b14b77dc4a686ac812fb495"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 410857 - Part 2: DrainOverflowLines before ResolveBidi for slightly improved performance. r=jfkthame, a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/nsBlockFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "720cbc37da356c260e60c8caf4170bdb5a66d914", "parents": ["4619a89b7f733e17ed7968bc7cdbcecdaaf6c9f5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 410857 - Part 3: Cache the PresContext instead of fetching it for every paragraph. r=jfkthame, a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/base/nsBidiPresUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b3fc8d044dec7a8af9f20b9afebb849387751415", "parents": ["720cbc37da356c260e60c8caf4170bdb5a66d914"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 410857 - Part 4: Stop passing around aBlockFrame just for DEBUG purposes.  Introduce BidiParagraphData::mCurrentBlock for that purpose and set it to the right block continuation this time. r=jfkthame, a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/base/nsBidiPresUtils.cpp", "layout/base/nsBidiPresUtils.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0316bb85a29c03cdc70f74598678bce3a0998c1f", "parents": ["b3fc8d044dec7a8af9f20b9afebb849387751415"], "tags": []}], "date": 1487695953, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6959": {"changesets": [{"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1338522 - Add telemetry for UI responsiveness during import of profile data from another browser. r=francois,Gijs a=jcristau", "files": ["browser/components/migration/MigrationUtils.jsm", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json", "toolkit/modules/ResponsivenessMonitor.jsm", "toolkit/modules/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c8cefb50d5a80b546777cc712d4de17ca92154f3", "parents": ["0316bb85a29c03cdc70f74598678bce3a0998c1f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1487762223, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "dgottwald@mozilla.com"}, "6960": {"changesets": [{"author": "Blake Kaplan \u003cmrbkap@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1307015 - Remove CPOWs from browser_bug623893.js. r=felipe, a=test-only\n\nIt took me a little bit to understand what the test was doing. It was actually\nusing the default tab to navigate to three pages. Then, it duplicated it\nimmediatedly closed that tab. Finally, it duplicated the original tab, then\nduplicated the duplicate before closing both of those tabs.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 85eY3FhZniA", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/general/browser_bug623893.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "60618c6f74d22b886b776403876e7acb6e42aeab", "parents": ["c8cefb50d5a80b546777cc712d4de17ca92154f3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1303094 - make SourceSurfaceSkia allocation fallible by using sk_malloc. r=mchang a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7l3fOG0kkq0", "files": ["gfx/2d/SourceSurfaceSkia.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9170cc2ab18df31eaf7fffc5b6b5a26ebcbb4ec3", "parents": ["60618c6f74d22b886b776403876e7acb6e42aeab"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Keeler \u003cdkeeler@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1330043 - Disable SHA-1 in signatures on certificates issued by publicly-trusted roots. r=jcj, a=jcristau\n\nUnfortunately, this doesn't cover delegated OCSP responder certificates. While\ngathering telemetry on the use of SHA-1, we encountered bug 1183822 (basically,\nthat the method of gathering telemetry was causing OCSP verification failures\ndue to delegated responders signed with SHA-1). As a temporary solution, we\nchanged the verifier to always allow SHA-1 for OCSP certificates when verifying\nan OCSP response. Consequently, we now have no idea what the compatibility\nimpact of disabling SHA-1 in OCSP responder certificates will be, so it's\nprobably not a good idea to do that right now.\n\nEven if someone does manage to forge an OCSP responder certificate using a SHA-1\ncollision, they will have about as much power as an active network attacker\nblocking OCSP requests or injecting bad stapled OCSP responses, so this isn't a\ndisaster.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 10r23W1APiR", "files": ["netwerk/base/security-prefs.js", "security/certverifier/CertVerifier.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3aaf82595ea5f1b6270741b70f4a394103a4150a", "parents": ["9170cc2ab18df31eaf7fffc5b6b5a26ebcbb4ec3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andr\u00e9 Bargull \u003candre.bargull@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1333197 - Lazily initialize default timezone in DateTimeFormat prototype. r=Waldo, a=jcristau", "files": ["js/src/builtin/Intl.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "094a86d66f7616c79d5502f27c4556d91e1aea52", "parents": ["3aaf82595ea5f1b6270741b70f4a394103a4150a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Valentin Gosu \u003cvalentin.gosu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1337629 - Restrict allowed hostname characters. r=mcmanus, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: H8u2C5oSiT9", "files": ["netwerk/base/nsStandardURL.cpp", "netwerk/test/unit/test_standardurl.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "627d5544b9c047c09943fd5a4bee683fdf41172a", "parents": ["094a86d66f7616c79d5502f27c4556d91e1aea52"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Hao \u003cjhao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334468 - A crashtest about restricted characters in URI. r=mcmanus, a=test-only", "files": ["netwerk/test/crashtests/1334468-1.html", "netwerk/test/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dd602dd794e8cf7124e353f9ad6e8bd3ed2e7421", "parents": ["627d5544b9c047c09943fd5a4bee683fdf41172a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Henning \u003cjh+bugzilla@buttercookie.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1337264 - Don't depend on page title changes for updating the displayed URL. r=sebastian, a=jcristau\n\nWe've been displaying the URL in place of the page title in the toolbar for quite some time now, but still had the old logic in place whereby only title changes would trigger an update of the displayed text. Most of the time this works fine, because\n- page navigation usually goes hand in hand with a DOMTitleChanged event, and\n- when our loading progress bar stops, we update the displayed text anyway\n\nhowever a page doing its navigation in-place using some fancy JS logic and the corresponding history APIs etc. can bypass both of these provisions, since it might trigger neither a title change nor a full browser-side page load.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KRrTSmz1xxi", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/toolbar/BrowserToolbar.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ddf62df9e2e20833218f05a844615e846ab4d64f", "parents": ["dd602dd794e8cf7124e353f9ad6e8bd3ed2e7421"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1336467 - Don't blacken weakmap key unless both the delegate and the map are black. r=mccr8, a=jcristau", "files": ["xpcom/base/CycleCollectedJSContext.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e48cd1b9b444927fe3c6b5d68a5871061c54a1df", "parents": ["ddf62df9e2e20833218f05a844615e846ab4d64f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henri Sivonen \u003chsivonen@hsivonen.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334246. r=mrbkap, a=jcristau\n\nnsScannerString changes by erahm.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6lh8SYjpGlj", "files": ["parser/htmlparser/nsParser.cpp", "parser/htmlparser/nsScanner.cpp", "parser/htmlparser/nsScanner.h", "parser/htmlparser/nsScannerString.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ed33bb3a76d34c73a67c13a309236ca4b5380f8a", "parents": ["e48cd1b9b444927fe3c6b5d68a5871061c54a1df"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henri Sivonen \u003chsivonen@hsivonen.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1334290 - Remove useless fields from nsScanner. r=mrbkap, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6LnvmOGrGwz", "files": ["parser/htmlparser/nsExpatDriver.cpp", "parser/htmlparser/nsParser.cpp", "parser/htmlparser/nsScanner.cpp", "parser/htmlparser/nsScanner.h", "parser/htmlparser/nsScannerString.cpp", "parser/htmlparser/nsScannerString.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c17f3d7837f05b322d05557d2ec521bb47c327cc", "parents": ["ed33bb3a76d34c73a67c13a309236ca4b5380f8a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Kew \u003cjkew@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1295299 - Cherry-pick harfbuzz fix 44f7d6ecde9bf7427a05cbe73ed5d668b8a72b2a. r=jrmuizel, a=jcristau", "files": ["gfx/harfbuzz/src/hb-ot-layout-gsubgpos-private.hh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "10bce9625147fe39903884dfe20c04eb7f899a98", "parents": ["c17f3d7837f05b322d05557d2ec521bb47c327cc"], "tags": []}], "date": 1487783819, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6961": {"changesets": [{"author": "Paul Adenot \u003cpaul@paul.cx\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1228226 - Backed out changeset 2553c3b5ba89. a=jcristau\n\nThis causes a number of issues, like bug 1329082, where we don't swap the\nmessage queues of the MSG where we should, and blows up an assert in debug.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2I3IjfK8L8r", "files": ["dom/media/MediaStreamGraph.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "67ec955c09a072d5ce0f310ac28c78e1775dc8c0", "parents": ["10bce9625147fe39903884dfe20c04eb7f899a98"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1312981, bug 1313136 - Skip browser_capture_doorhanger_window_open.js on Linux for frequent failures. a=test-only", "files": ["toolkit/components/passwordmgr/test/browser/browser.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2c308b73cf7dbb3d655247143a2803f39ec33f01", "parents": ["67ec955c09a072d5ce0f310ac28c78e1775dc8c0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew McCreight \u003ccontinuation@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1336811 - Clear mWaitingForOnStopRequest in CloseRequest. r=smaug a=jcristau\n\nOtherwise, if a tab is closed when we have a request pending, we'll\nend up leaking the page forever, due to CC optimizations.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: E5NC0jxWCur", "files": ["dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestMainThread.cpp", "dom/xhr/tests/browser.ini", "dom/xhr/tests/browser_xhr_onchange_leak.html", "dom/xhr/tests/browser_xhr_onchange_leak.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "50ee31c6c5ce16592f8ce4217525238e55b5f93f", "parents": ["2c308b73cf7dbb3d655247143a2803f39ec33f01"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henry Chang \u003chchang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1313711 - Fix track element CORS bug. r=dveditz, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: SRWbiIuUdt", "files": ["dom/html/HTMLTrackElement.cpp", "toolkit/components/url-classifier/tests/mochitest/basic.vtt^headers^", "toolkit/components/url-classifier/tests/mochitest/mochitest.ini", "toolkit/components/url-classifier/tests/mochitest/seek.webm", "toolkit/components/url-classifier/tests/mochitest/test_classify_track.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "37d108f28d69fd4171f9b94f2840e5bbf71fc6f9", "parents": ["50ee31c6c5ce16592f8ce4217525238e55b5f93f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Banner \u003cstandard8@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1341338 - feedType is undefined in FeedConverter#handleResult. r=jaws, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: tZAdpmkNWp", "files": ["browser/components/feeds/FeedConverter.js", "browser/components/feeds/content/subscribe.js", "browser/components/feeds/content/subscribe.xhtml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "08169479d28fb049c61104dff59f71f030fee0da", "parents": ["37d108f28d69fd4171f9b94f2840e5bbf71fc6f9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alessio Placitelli \u003calessio.placitelli@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1338099 - Fix the source packager to produce a non empty sourcestamp.txt file. r=ted, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1DsBkS1eSX8", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/installer/packager.mk"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "484c20783a1b530cc00c9e2a2cd93ebf3026d2e3", "parents": ["08169479d28fb049c61104dff59f71f030fee0da"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Benjamin Bouvier \u003cbenj@benj.me\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1341080 - Provide an empty filename if the wasm caller doesn't have one in DescribeScriptedCaller. r=luke, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8h0NbN7jOBq", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/wasm/regress/null-metadata-filename.js", "js/src/jsapi.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6d4cf63783345d0c22410cdf09424487046f8c7f", "parents": ["484c20783a1b530cc00c9e2a2cd93ebf3026d2e3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1339643 - Add English Yandex search engine to en-US/GB for testing. r=flod a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LGokLUsKb85", "files": ["browser/locales/jar.mn", "browser/locales/search/list.json", "browser/locales/searchplugins/images/yandex-en.ico", "browser/locales/searchplugins/yandex-en.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2cfe593873d0d88aa99b8402cd2351ce4d913f93", "parents": ["6d4cf63783345d0c22410cdf09424487046f8c7f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nathan Froyd \u003cfroydnj@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1339617 - Move GetClosure call prior to canceling timer. r=mayhemer, a=jcristau\n\nSome recent work on timers changed how we handle callbacks and\nassociated closure data: prior to these changes, canceling timers would\nnot null out associated closure data, so calling GetClosure() on a timer\nafter canceling it would return what you had put in.  After these\nchanges, however, GetClosure() after cancellation would retrieve a null\nvalue, causing anything that assumed non-nullness to crash.  The simple\nfix is to move the GetClosure() call prior to Cancel()'ing the timer.", "files": ["netwerk/cache/nsDeleteDir.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4a51d1339b8f658f7b80d8f9d07d81122a0aeaf6", "parents": ["2cfe593873d0d88aa99b8402cd2351ce4d913f93"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan-Ivar Bruaroey \u003cjib@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1341409 - Fix omission of advanced constraints in applying camera constraints. r=jesup, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2qhuv5e6lv9", "files": ["dom/media/webrtc/MediaTrackConstraints.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5e8888436efbedd01db019a5fd503795f3c8fdac", "parents": ["4a51d1339b8f658f7b80d8f9d07d81122a0aeaf6"], "tags": []}], "date": 1487786953, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6962": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1311239 - Skip HSTS priming mochitests on debug builds since they're timeout-prone and not shipping in this release. a=test-only", "files": ["dom/security/test/hsts/browser.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "503ac51dde21933eca73532fd8f948cb1f9a7f4f", "parents": ["5e8888436efbedd01db019a5fd503795f3c8fdac"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jeff Muizelaar \u003cjmuizelaar@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335149 - Remove unnecessary flush() calls from canvas implementation. r=bas, a=jcristau\n\nFlushing should usually be done by the moz2d backend unless we're accessing\nthe data through other mechanisms.", "files": ["dom/canvas/CanvasRenderingContext2D.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxContext.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e2a6d2b4f1b4b8e0c77d057bc012fb20a18df2f5", "parents": ["503ac51dde21933eca73532fd8f948cb1f9a7f4f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1487810612, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6963": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD520b4_2017022301_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1322027 - Update jemalloc 4 to version 4.4.0. r=glandium a=jorgk", "files": ["build/autoconf/jemalloc.m4", "memory/jemalloc/src/ChangeLog", "memory/jemalloc/src/INSTALL", "memory/jemalloc/src/Makefile.in", "memory/jemalloc/src/VERSION", "memory/jemalloc/src/build-aux/config.guess", "memory/jemalloc/src/build-aux/config.sub", "memory/jemalloc/src/configure", "memory/jemalloc/src/configure.ac", "memory/jemalloc/src/doc/jemalloc.xml.in", "memory/jemalloc/src/include/jemalloc/internal/arena.h", "memory/jemalloc/src/include/jemalloc/internal/chunk.h", "memory/jemalloc/src/include/jemalloc/internal/extent.h", "memory/jemalloc/src/include/jemalloc/internal/jemalloc_internal.h.in", "memory/jemalloc/src/include/jemalloc/internal/jemalloc_internal_defs.h.in", "memory/jemalloc/src/include/jemalloc/internal/pages.h", "memory/jemalloc/src/include/jemalloc/internal/private_symbols.txt", "memory/jemalloc/src/include/jemalloc/internal/stats.h", "memory/jemalloc/src/include/jemalloc/internal/util.h", "memory/jemalloc/src/include/jemalloc/internal/valgrind.h", "memory/jemalloc/src/msvc/projects/vc2015/test_threads/test_threads.cpp", "memory/jemalloc/src/src/arena.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/src/base.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/src/chunk.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/src/chunk_dss.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/src/extent.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/src/huge.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/src/jemalloc.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/src/pages.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/src/stats.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/src/tcache.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/src/util.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/integration/MALLOCX_ARENA.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/integration/allocated.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/integration/chunk.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/integration/mallocx.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/integration/overflow.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/integration/rallocx.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/integration/sdallocx.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/integration/thread_arena.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/integration/thread_tcache_enabled.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/integration/xallocx.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/arena_reset.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/decay.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/mallctl.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/pack.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/pages.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/prof_accum.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/prof_active.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/prof_gdump.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/prof_idump.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/prof_reset.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/prof_thread_name.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/run_quantize.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/size_classes.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/stats.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/tsd.c", "memory/jemalloc/src/test/unit/util.c", "memory/jemalloc/upstream.info"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f16cb150ab1a1e0111fc2a090f4f90e3990b7252", "parents": ["e2a6d2b4f1b4b8e0c77d057bc012fb20a18df2f5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD520b4_2017022301_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1322027 - Don't disable hugepage support since it no longer causes PGO issues. a=jorgk", "files": ["build/autoconf/jemalloc.m4"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "86f9d651515ca2c2f9aeb1326dd1862bd84114be", "parents": ["f16cb150ab1a1e0111fc2a090f4f90e3990b7252"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD520b4_2017022301_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1311039 - Properly detect the default malloc zone on OSX 10.12. r=njn a=jorgk", "files": ["memory/mozjemalloc/jemalloc.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "430b7db26dea74d30cf9e648e8c004c6e2d45f4f", "parents": ["86f9d651515ca2c2f9aeb1326dd1862bd84114be"], "tags": []}, {"author": "John Paul Adrian Glaubitz \u003cglaubitz@physik.fu-berlin.de\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD520b4_2017022301_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1275204 - mozjemalloc: Use better pre-processor defines for sparc64. r=glandium a=jorgk", "files": ["memory/mozjemalloc/jemalloc.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "515a69cf806caf09b81e21bc12b51b1bd6822414", "parents": ["430b7db26dea74d30cf9e648e8c004c6e2d45f4f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "John Paul Adrian Glaubitz \u003cglaubitz@physik.fu-berlin.de\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD520b4_2017022301_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1275204 - mozjemalloc: Use the JS arm64 allocator on Linux/sparc64. r=glandium a=jorgk", "files": ["memory/mozjemalloc/jemalloc.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1da1471e744436c4d0bfb8225820e576896aaa21", "parents": ["515a69cf806caf09b81e21bc12b51b1bd6822414"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD520b4_2017022301_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1286613 - Properly call mozjemalloc pre/post fork hooks on OSX when replace-malloc is enabled. r=njn a=jorgk\n\nSomehow, we never called those hooks when replace-malloc is enabled. I'd\nexpect this to cause random deadlocks when forking, and I'm surprised\nthis hasn't surfaced. Maybe it actually causes some intermittent oranges\non automation, who knows.\n\nThis also brings consistency with what is done for jemalloc 4, and with\nthe mozjemalloc implementation, too, that we're going to replace with\nthis one in a subsequent changeset.", "files": ["memory/build/replace_malloc.c", "memory/mozjemalloc/jemalloc.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bdfde6aa500a5064675fd658c7d93def48b13f56", "parents": ["1da1471e744436c4d0bfb8225820e576896aaa21"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD520b4_2017022301_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1286613 - Move replace-malloc zone allocator to a separate file. r=njn a=jorgk\n\nThe intent here is to reuse the zone allocator for mozjemalloc, to avoid\nall the shortcomings of mozjemalloc using a different one. This change\nonly moves the replace-malloc zone allocator out of replace-malloc.c, to\nmake changes for mozjemalloc integration clearer.", "files": ["memory/build/moz.build", "memory/build/replace_malloc.c", "memory/build/zone.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a0b9ad6f52df422c6acb52b916355ba21882c5de", "parents": ["bdfde6aa500a5064675fd658c7d93def48b13f56"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD520b4_2017022301_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1286613 - Use the same zone allocator implementation as replace-malloc for mozjemalloc. r=njn a=jorgk\n\nWe have been using a different zone allocator between mozjemalloc and\nreplace-malloc for a long time. Jemalloc 4 uses the same as\nreplace-malloc, albeit as part of the jemalloc upstream code base.\n\nWe've been bitten many times in the past with Apple changes breaking the\nzone allocator, and each time we've had to make changes to the three\ninstances, although two of them are similar and the changes there are\nstraightforward.\n\nIt also turns out that the way the mozjemalloc zone allocator is set up,\nwhen a new version of OSX appears with a new version of the system zone\nallocator, Firefox ends up using the system allocator, because the zone\nallocator version is not supported.\n\nSo, we use the same zone allocator for both replace-malloc and\nmozjemalloc, making everything on par with jemalloc 4.", "files": ["memory/build/moz.build", "memory/build/zone.c", "memory/mozjemalloc/jemalloc.c", "memory/mozjemalloc/osx_zone_types.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "15a52512ffbd96987eaa7e8a308efcf7193e086d", "parents": ["a0b9ad6f52df422c6acb52b916355ba21882c5de"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD520b4_2017022301_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1286613 - Don't rely on OSX SDK malloc/malloc.h for malloc_zone struct definitions. r=njn a=jorgk\n\nThe SDK jemalloc is built against might be not be the latest for various\nreasons, but the resulting binary ought to work on newer versions of\nOSX.\n\nIn order to ensure this, we need the fullest definitions possible, so\ncopy what we need from the latest version of malloc/malloc.h available\non opensource.apple.com.\n\n[Adapted from\nhttps://github.com/jemalloc/jemalloc/commit/c68bb4179312665e22d375aecf9f4306607c7c1a]", "files": ["memory/build/zone.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4b50594f88dc619cc6f4097c943a37881e8ee568", "parents": ["15a52512ffbd96987eaa7e8a308efcf7193e086d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD520b4_2017022301_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1286613 - Add dummy implementations for most remaining OSX zone allocator functions. r=njn a=jorgk\n\nSome system libraries are using malloc_default_zone() and then using\nsome of the malloc_zone_* API. Under normal conditions, those functions\ncheck the malloc_zone_t/malloc_introspection_t struct for the values\nthat are allowed to be NULL, so that a NULL deref doesn't happen.\n\nAs of OSX 10.12, malloc_default_zone() doesn't return the actual default\nzone anymore, but returns a fake, wrapper zone. The wrapper zone defines\nall the possible functions in the malloc_zone_t/malloc_introspection_t\nstruct (almost), and calls the function from the registered default zone\n(jemalloc in our case) on its own. Without checking whether the pointers\nare NULL.\n\nThis means that a system library that calls e.g.\nmalloc_zone_batch_malloc(malloc_default_zone(), ...) ends up trying to\ncall jemalloc_zone.batch_malloc, which is NULL, and crash follows.\n\nSo as of OSX 10.12, the default zone is required to have all the\nfunctions available (really, the same as the wrapper zone), even if they\ndo nothing.\n\nThis is arguably a bug in libsystem_malloc in OSX 10.12, but jemalloc\nstill needs to work in that case.\n\n[Adapted from\nhttps://github.com/jemalloc/jemalloc/commit/c6943acb3c56d1b3d1e82dd43b3fcfeae7771990]", "files": ["memory/build/zone.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "90002c92a0ef798079dbfc5b5b611d84b81464aa", "parents": ["4b50594f88dc619cc6f4097c943a37881e8ee568"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD520b4_2017022301_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1286613 - Update jemalloc 4 to c6943ac. r=njn a=jorgk\n\nThis picks the same changes as the ones we just did to\nmemory/build/zone.c, plus a oneliner for sparc64.", "files": ["memory/jemalloc/src/VERSION", "memory/jemalloc/src/configure", "memory/jemalloc/src/configure.ac", "memory/jemalloc/src/include/jemalloc/internal/jemalloc_internal.h.in", "memory/jemalloc/src/include/jemalloc/internal/jemalloc_internal_defs.h.in", "memory/jemalloc/src/include/jemalloc/internal/mb.h", "memory/jemalloc/src/src/zone.c", "memory/jemalloc/upstream.info"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3d63c41abefea382a55eab2d438d021bb10fd597", "parents": ["90002c92a0ef798079dbfc5b5b611d84b81464aa"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD520b4_2017022301_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1332508 - Reinitialize allocator mutexes in fork() child processes. r=njn a=jorgk DONTBUILD\n\nAdapted from\nhttps://github.com/jemalloc/jemalloc/commit/4e2e3dd9cf19ed5991938a708a8b50611aa5bbf8\nand\nhttps://github.com/jemalloc/jemalloc/commit/d9f7b2a4307f7ff9f7a139b33d366d44e8a8b83d\n\nAs per the latter commit, it would seem unlocking, in fork() child\nprocesses, mutexes that were locked in the parent process is not really\nwell supported on OSX 10.12. The addition of the zone_reinit_lock\nfunction in 10.12 supports this idea.", "files": ["memory/build/zone.c", "memory/mozjemalloc/jemalloc.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7659278b0a9bb59075aeb1f6d78b16b1abb4eba8", "parents": ["3d63c41abefea382a55eab2d438d021bb10fd597"], "tags": []}], "date": 1487856764, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "mozilla@jorgk.com"}, "6964": {"changesets": [{"author": "Rail Aliiev \u003crail@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1337366 - SHA1 repacks configs for ESR52 r=jlund a=release DONTBUILD\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LM1wuXGLtn3", "files": ["testing/mozharness/configs/partner_repacks/staging_release_mozilla-esr52_desktop.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8f3d880fd1b1ffe2f627831e93da37821346e13d", "parents": ["e2a6d2b4f1b4b8e0c77d057bc012fb20a18df2f5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1487861796, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "raliiev@mozilla.com"}, "6965": {"changesets": [{"author": "Gabor Krizsanits \u003cgkrizsanits@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1337354 - Fix races in referrer tests. r=mrbkap, a=test-only", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/referrer/browser_referrer_middle_click.js", "browser/base/content/test/referrer/browser_referrer_middle_click_in_container.js", "browser/base/content/test/referrer/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1175a6a517a66b2b856bd725beb66f09d71d04b0", "parents": ["8f3d880fd1b1ffe2f627831e93da37821346e13d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1257366 - Try setting designMode again. r=gbrown, a=test-only\n\nIf the first set designMode call fails, schedule another call for a later time.", "files": ["mobile/android/tests/browser/robocop/robocop_input.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "98f9ac8d96054321882345dc9c5016332c621f31", "parents": ["1175a6a517a66b2b856bd725beb66f09d71d04b0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Blake Kaplan \u003cmrbkap@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335801 - Actually wait for the right href to load. r=Felipe, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GVkWzNoTSQ7", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/referrer/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8d44efe8389de41697165532de6feaa405b39231", "parents": ["98f9ac8d96054321882345dc9c5016332c621f31"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Robert Strong \u003crobert.bugzilla@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1320590 - Remove reportError for microcode detection since AMD cpu's don't always have the registry key that is checked. r=felipc, a=jcristau", "files": ["browser/extensions/aushelper/bootstrap.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b5ac5fb65aba3598a0855930c0f28a3f19a2325b", "parents": ["8d44efe8389de41697165532de6feaa405b39231"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Robert Strong \u003crobert.bugzilla@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1329692 - Ship updated Firefox system add-on to change app.update.url preference for Websense with new endpoint version check. r=felipc, r=bsmedberg for data, a=jcristau", "files": ["browser/extensions/aushelper/bootstrap.js", "browser/extensions/aushelper/install.rdf.in", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Scalars.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fb4e4e5f4d698e9f55efe5a798615b1cf7ae705f", "parents": ["b5ac5fb65aba3598a0855930c0f28a3f19a2325b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335827 - Clean gtk window's surface provider before it gets destroyed. r=karlt, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5Aahub11ZRF", "files": ["widget/gtk/nsWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "61d165ab850743d67e4389de201d9110ace08ded", "parents": ["fb4e4e5f4d698e9f55efe5a798615b1cf7ae705f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1487863115, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6966": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1329692 - Remove unknown \"record_in_processes\" field from Scalars.yaml. r=Dexter, a=bustage", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/Scalars.yaml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6bff957177d230950b59c95bc8d126809c71ce39", "parents": ["61d165ab850743d67e4389de201d9110ace08ded"], "tags": []}], "date": 1487864361, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "6967": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.c